Vim

My Mappings:
   • .va     —  Select all text
   • ,gu     —  Toggle gundo
   • ,nt     —  Toggle NERDTree
   • ,nu     —  Toggle numbering method
   • ,ff     —  FuzzyFinder File opener
   • ,fb     —  FuzzyFinder buffer opener
   • ,fd     —  FuzzyFinder Directory opener
   • ,cc     —  Close Window
   • ,bb     —  Open bookmarks.note file
   • ,rr     —  Re Tabs a file, removes /t and extra spaces
   • ,ls     —  Puts a file listing of current directory in the current buffer       
   • ,gor    —  Run go source
   • ,goc    —  Build go source
   • <F6>    —  List buffers
Cool Commands:
   • gf      —  Goto File for system Directories, Notes or Text documents
   • K       —  Goto Manual page or pydoc
   • go      —  HTTP, FTP Links and Complex Documents(PDF, ODC, ...)
   • gO      —  Opens a html file in current buffer in web browser
   • gt      —  Goto next tab
   • gn      —  Create a file from word under cursor
   • gb      —  Goto next buffer
   • gB      —  Goto previous buffer
   • <C-W>gf —  Opens file in a new tab
   • :n*.txt —  Open Multiple Files
References:
  • Bookmarks.note
  • OpeningNote.note
